==English==
===Verb===
'''to snitch''' ([[snitches]], [[snitched]], [[snitching]])

# To steal, quickly and quietly 
# To inform

====Translations====
*German: [[klauen]] (1)
*Spanish: [[robar]], [[mangar]] (1), [[chivarse]] (2)

===Noun===
'''snitch''' ([[snitches]])

# A thief
# An informer, usually one who betrays his group
# A nose (''usage: An [[itchy]] snitch'')
# (''Harry Potter'') A golden ball with silver wings used in the game of [[Quidditch]].

====Synonyms====
# An informer - [[grass]]

